<subSubSection lastPageId="34" lastPageNumber="235" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,1407,2010]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,365,1695,1722]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">Redescription</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[380,500,1695,1722]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">FEMALE</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[515,598,1695,1722]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–20" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[156,1431,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 11–20. Phytomia spp., habitus, lateral view. 11. P. curta (Loew) ♂ 12. P. pallida sp. nov. ♂ 13. P. erratica (Bezzi) ♂ 14. P. fucoides Bezzi ♂ 15. P. fusca Hull ♀ 16. P. incisa (Wiedemann) ♂ 17. P. varians Curran ♂ 18. P. melas (Bezzi) ♂ 19. P. poensis (Bezzi) ♂ 20 (copyright NRMS). P. fronto (Loew) ♀" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3909051" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3909051/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[619,681,1695,1722]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[696,780,1695,1722]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–28" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[281,1316,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[271,1316,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 21–28. Figs 21–26. Phytomia spp., head, dorsal view. 21. P. bullata (Loew) ♀ 22. P. aurigera Bezzi ♀ 23. P. serena (Curran) ♀ 24. P. fusca Hull ♀ 25. P. incisa (Wiedemann) ♂ 27. P. poensis (Bezzi) ♂ Figs 27–28. Phytomia spp., head, lateral view. 27. P. incisa (Wiedemann) ♀ 28. P. poensis (Bezzi) ♀" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3909053" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3909053/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
). Eye bare; dichoptic, facets equal size. Frons dark ground colour, with dense golden yellow pollinosity; covered with dense pile of medium long golden yellow pile; rugose area shining yellow-orange to dark orange, occupying one-third of entire width and equal in height to 1.5 times length of ocellar triangle. Face as frons, ventral part around oral margin and on gena shining black with dispersed greyish pollinosity and without distinct pile; facial tubercle oval shaped, weakly developed. Vertex with orangebrown pubescence and dark yellow medium long pile; continued along occiput, anterior margin in ventral two-thirds conspicuously silvery pollinosity, ventrally with dispersed pale pile. Antennal segments golden yellow to orange; arista dark yellow, in basal two-thirds with medium long pile equal to half the width of pedicel.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,1407,2010]" lastBlockId="34.[151,1437,153,791]" lastPageId="34" lastPageNumber="235" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,288,1984,2010]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">Thorax</emphasis>
. Scutum black ground colour, with dense greyish brown pollinosity, anteriorly more greyish; covered with dense pile of long golden yellow to orange pilosity. Scutellum rufous, with long orange to rufous pilosity. Pleural sclerites black, covered with dense pile of long black pile except meron, anterior part of katepisternum and anterior anepisternum; dorsal margin of posterior anepisternum broadly with orange pilosity.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,153,791]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,255,261,287]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">Legs</emphasis>
. Predominantly black, except tarsal segment where yellow-orange. Fore and mid leg, femora with dense short black pilosity, posteriorly longer; tibia silvery in basal half dorsally, ventrally less so; with short black pilosity, except in silvery part where pale. Hind leg, femur dorsally and ventrally conspicuous dense black pilosity, in basal ventral two-thirds longer and more dispersed; silvery part on tibia restricted to dorsal side and for basal fifth at most, dorsally and ventrally with conspicuous dense black pilosity over entire length, except in silvery part where pale.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,153,791]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,264,440,467]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[281,368,440,467]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–60" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,203,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[157,1431,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 49–60. Phytomia spp., right wing. 49. P. pubipennis Bezzi ♀ 50. P. natalensis (Macquart) ♂ 51. P. curta (Loew) ♂ 52. P. pallida sp. nov. ♂ 53. P. erratica (Bezzi) ♂ 54. P. fucoides Bezzi ♂ 55. P. fusca Hull ♀ 56. P. incisa (Wiedemann) ♂ 57. P. varians Curran ♂ 58. P. melas (Bezzi) ♂ 59. P. melas (Bezzi) ♀ 60. P. poensis (Bezzi) ♀" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3909059" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3909059/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">Fig. 55</figureCitation>
). Mainly hyaline; slightly fumose at base and in apical part of cell 
<emphasis box="[1142,1154,442,467]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">c</emphasis>
. More distinct brownish patch, consisting of microtrichia, in medial part of wing anteriorly from apex of vein 
<emphasis box="[1119,1145,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">Sc</emphasis>
, posteriorly along medial part of cell 
<emphasis box="[283,294,514,539]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">r</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[293,301,530,544]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">
<subScript attach="left" box="[293,301,530,544]" fontSize="6" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">1</subScript>
</emphasis>
, basal part of cell 
<emphasis box="[514,525,514,539]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">r</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[525,552,530,544]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">
<subScript attach="left" box="[525,552,530,544]" fontSize="6" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">2+3</subScript>
</emphasis>
, and into cell 
<taxonomicName box="[716,802,513,539]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="where">
<emphasis box="[716,727,514,539]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">r</emphasis>
where
</taxonomicName>
it reaches the junction of vein 
<emphasis box="[1156,1179,514,539]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">M</emphasis>
with crossvein 
<emphasis box="[1359,1429,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">bm-cu</emphasis>
. Calypters pale yellowish; with fringe of pale orange pile.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,153,791]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,316,584,611]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[334,422,585,611]" captionStart="FIGURES 73–84" captionStartId="30.[151,264,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[182,1431,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[156,1431,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURES 73–84. Phytomia spp., abdomen, dorsal view. 73. P. curta (Loew) ♂ 74. P. pallida sp. nov. ♂ 75. P. erratica (Bezzi) ♂ 76. P. fucoides Bezzi ♀ 77. P. fusca Hull ♀ 78. P. incisa (Wiedemann) ♂ 79. P. varians Curran ♀ 80. P. melas (Bezzi) ♂ 81- 82. P. melas (Bezzi) ♀; 83. P. poensis (Bezzi) ♂ 84. P. poensis (Bezzi) ♀" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3909063" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3909063/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">Fig. 77</figureCitation>
). Mainly shining black, partially with black pollinosity; with pair of large semi-circular orange maculae on tergum 2; no distinct bullae. Pilosity short to medium long dispersed black; pilosity on maculae and along anterior margin of tergum 2 denser golden-yellow. Sterna shining black; with widely dispersed long black pile.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,153,791]" box="[199,415,728,755]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,283,728,755]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">MALE</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
